    "CMIN/df is one of the fundamental fit indices testing the overall adequacy of the obtained model.",
    "The resulting outcome is marginally above the acceptable limit (≤ 5).",
    "According to McIntosh (2007), even if the model is correct, there is a possibility that the CMIN/ df index may indicate that the model is inadequate.",
    "This is because CMIN/df is highly sensitive to sample size.",
    "Therefore, when large samples are used, it is likely that the model will be rejected almost every time (Bentler & Bonnet, 1980)."
